TYPE: Test,
TARGET: Control Module 3 switch contacts and series path,
DESCRIPTION: With power applied and all other modules ON, open Control Module 3 and, using an ohmmeter or continuity tester with power temporarily removed, check the resistance between the incoming 12V node and the outgoing 12V node across the switch in both positions. Then repeat with power applied by measuring voltage at the outgoing 12V node (toward module 4) relative to battery negative. This will confirm whether the internal series path through the switch of Module 3 is open even when the switch is in the ON position.,
RESULT: Control Switch 3 shows nominal continuity (0.01 Ω), but nearby anomaly indicates Control Input Cable (+) 3 has a disconnected, floating end that was originally connected to the switch. With power applied, Control Output Cable (+) 3 measures ~0.0064 V relative to battery negative, effectively zero.
