2026-04-16 12:13:52 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control Module 3 internal 12V series connection (input (+) lead to switch contact)'] hypothesis_explanation='Measurements show 12 V present on Control Input Cable (+) 3 relative to battery negative, but both the internal 12 V line after the supposed connection and the indicator branch sit at ~0 V, and the output (+) of Module 3 is also at ~0 V. The continuity test indicates the switch itself is good, but an anomaly was observed: Control Input Cable (+) 3 has a disconnected, floating end that should be joined to the switch. This means the incoming +12 V is not actually connected into Module 3’s series path. As a result, +12 V stops at the loose input lead, and all downstream modules (3–8 and the load) see no supply, explaining why their LEDs and the lamp are off. The root cause is therefore an open circuit inside Control Module 3 between the input (+) conductor and the switch/series path (e.g., broken or detached internal connection). Repairing/restoring this specific internal 12 V connection will restore operation downstream.'
